reviews.text: Passable taste and service
Great value and amazingly fast service. Only a few menu items are tasty, such as the laksa. Most others are bland.

Simply put: Do not eat here! I have been to this restaurant numerous times. And the standard and quality drops with each visit. 

When they first opened 2 years ago, the portions of chicken were generous. Then it got reduced to decent. Then the quality of the chicken dropped from juicy to dry. And now it's just a small portion of dry chicken and no oily chicken rice!

For $53, I get better food at Macs or Cafe de Coral. NEVER EATING HERE AGAIN.
This was a good place when I used to go here but now the manager has changed.

The hainan chicken was dry, asked to get me ones. Waitress mocked us for being American saying the chicken was free range. If you're looking for a place to eat with your kids and want them to get stomach flu the next day. Come here. Otherwise go across to cafe de coral.
